e" data-rtl-flip="" class="icon-xs"><use href="/cdn/assets/sprites-core-0a715c44.svg#b140e7" fill="currentColor"></use></svg></button></div><div data-message-author-role="assistant" data-message-id="3cedd5f0-d4fe-48ab-89e3-88ede2d5a954" dir="auto" data-message-model-slug="gpt-5-5-thinking" class="min-h-8 text-message relative flex w-full flex-col items-end gap-2 text-start break-words whitespace-normal outline-none keyboard-focused:focus-ring [.text-message+&amp;]:mt-1"><div class="flex w-full flex-col gap-1 empty:hidden"><div class="markdown prose dark:prose-invert wrap-break-word w-full light markdown-new-styling"><p data-start="0" data-end="193">Yes — use those reference images <strong data-start="33" data-end="56">only as inspiration</strong>, not as “copy this exactly.” The goal is: <strong data-start="99" data-end="156">Poki/Brawl Stars/Subway Surfers-style homepage energy</strong>, but still original for Shift Panic.</p>
<p data-start="195" data-end="422">Below are <strong data-start="205" data-end="242">copy-paste-ready prompts in order</strong>. I would queue these <strong data-start="264" data-end="301">one at a time or in small batches</strong>, not all blindly, because homepage changes can easily break layout. But these are written to be safer and more specific.</p>
<hr data-start="424" data-end="427">
<h2 data-section-id="1bn51jw" data-start="429" data-end="473">RULES TO GIVE COPILOT BEFORE EVERY PROMPT</h2>
<p data-start="475" data-end="491">Copy this first:</p>
<pre class="overflow-visible! px-0!" data-start="493" data-end="1424"><div class="relative w-full mt-4 mb-1"><div class=""><div class="relative"><div class="h-full min-h-0 min-w-0"><div class="h-full min-h-0 min-w-0" style="width: 100%; transform: none;"><div class="border border-token-border-light border-radius-3xl corner-superellipse/1.1 rounded-3xl"><div class="h-full w-full border-radius-3xl bg-token-bg-elevated-secondary corner-superellipse/1.1 overflow-clip rounded-3xl lxnfua_clipPathFallback"><div class="pointer-events-none absolute end-1.5 top-1 z-2 md:end-2 md:top-1"><button type="button" class="flex gap-1 items-center select-none pointer-events-auto py-2 text-sm font-medium hover:bg-black/5 dark:hover:bg-white/10 size-9 rounded-full px-2" aria-label="Copy" data-state="closed"><svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" width="20" height="20" aria-hidden="true" class="icon-md"><use href="/cdn/assets/sprites-core-0a715c44.svg#ce3544" fill="currentColor"></use></svg></button></div><div class="relative"><div class="pe-11 pt-3" style="transform: none;"><div class="relative z-0 flex max-w-full"><div id="code-block-viewer" dir="ltr" class="q9tKkq_viewer cm-editor z-10 light:cm-light dark:cm-light flex h-full w-full flex-col items-stretch ͼd ͼr"><div class="cm-scroller"><pre class="cm-content q9tKkq_readonly m-0"><code><span>GLOBAL RULES FOR ALL CHANGES:</span><br><span>1. Do not erase or reset user progress, coins, unlocked skins, equipped items, lifetime score, best score, leaderboard data, challenge progress, or localStorage/Firebase data.</span><br><span>2. Preserve all existing gameplay logic unless the prompt specifically asks to change gameplay.</span><br><span>3. Do not break Endless, Panic Quest, Shop, Leaderboard, Help, Settings, or Game Over navigation.</span><br><span>4. Make changes incrementally and test after each change.</span><br><span>5. Keep the site working on desktop first. Mobile can be improved later.</span><br><span>6. If a file or function is unclear, inspect the codebase before editing.</span><br><span>7. Do not create duplicate UI elements or duplicate event listeners.</span><br><span>8. Do not add placeholder dead buttons. Every visible button must work.</span><br><span>9. Do not use copyrighted Brawl Stars/Subway Surfers/Poki assets. Only use original Shift Panic visuals.</span><br><span>10. After changes, verify the homepage loads with no console errors.</span></code></pre></div></div></div></div></div></div></div></div></div><div class=""><div class="" style="width: 100%; transform: none;"></div></div></div></div></div></pre>
<hr data-start="1426" data-end="1429">
<h1 data-section-id="1qo2jm3" data-start="1431" data-end="1478">PROMPT 1 — Homepage Layout Rebuild Foundation</h1>
<pre class="overflow-visible! px-0!" data-start="1480" data-end="3677"><div class="relative w-full mt-4 mb-1"><div class=""><div class="relative"><div class="h-full min-h-0 min-w-0"><div class="h-full min-h-0 min-w-0" style="width: 100%; transform: none;"><div class="border border-token-border-light border-radius-3xl corner-superellipse/1.1 rounded-3xl"><div class="h-full w-full border-radius-3xl bg-token-bg-elevated-secondary corner-superellipse/1.1 overflow-clip rounded-3xl lxnfua_clipPathFallback"><div class="pointer-events-none absolute end-1.5 top-1 z-2 md:end-2 md:top-1"><button type="button" class="flex gap-1 items-center select-none pointer-events-auto py-2 text-sm font-medium hover:bg-black/5 dark:hover:bg-white/10 size-9 rounded-full px-2" aria-label="Copy" data-state="closed"><svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" width="20" height="20" aria-hidden="true" class="icon-md"><use href="/cdn/assets/sprites-core-0a715c44.svg#ce3544" fill="currentColor"></use></svg></button></div><div class="relative"><div class="pe-11 pt-3" style="transform: none;"><div class="relative z-0 flex max-w-full"><div id="code-block-viewer" dir="ltr" class="q9tKkq_viewer cm-editor z-10 light:cm-light dark:cm-light flex h-full w-full flex-col items-stretch ͼd ͼr"><div class="cm-scroller"><pre class="cm-content q9tKkq_readonly m-0"><code><span>You are GitHub Copilot Agent working on Shift Panic. Rebuild the desktop homepage layout to feel like a professional Poki-quality arcade game menu, inspired by the energy of Brawl Stars/Subway Surfers/Geometry Dash but using only original Shift Panic visuals.</span><br><br><span>Current problem:</span><br><span>The homepage looks too empty, flat, and unprofessional. The title, stats, buttons, and cards feel stacked without strong hierarchy. The Play button is not dominant enough. The screen does not feel like a “game lobby.”</span><br><br><span>Goal:</span><br><span>Create a polished desktop-first homepage with a strong central hero panel, big Play button, visible progression, daily challenge, and clear secondary actions.</span><br><br><span>Required layout:</span><br><span>1. Full-screen animated background stays, but reduce visual clutter behind the main UI.</span><br><span>2. Create one large centered “hero/lobby card” with glassmorphism, rounded corners, soft glow, and subtle border.</span><br><span>3. Top section: large Shift Panic logo/title, subtitle, and 3 small feature chips:</span><br><span>   - Fast reflexes</span><br><span>   - Color chaos</span><br><span>   - Unlock skins</span><br><span>4. Center section: animated player orb/mascot preview on the left and gameplay preview card on the right.</span><br><span>5. Main action section: huge “PLAY ENDLESS” button, at least 30–40% bigger than current.</span><br><span>6. Secondary action: “PANIC QUEST” button below or beside it, visually exciting but clearly secondary.</span><br><span>7. Bottom action row: Multiplayer, Shop, Leaderboard, Help.</span><br><span>8. Stats should be visible but not dominate:</span><br><span>   - Best score</span><br><span>   - Coins</span><br><span>   - Lifetime score</span><br><span>   - Rank</span><br><span>9. Daily challenge should become a large, colorful card with a “Play Daily” button.</span><br><span>10. Everything should fit cleanly inside the first desktop viewport at 1920x1080 without requiring scroll to access primary buttons.</span><br><br><span>Important:</span><br><span>- Do not remove existing button functionality.</span><br><span>- Reuse existing route/menu handlers.</span><br><span>- Do not reset localStorage progress.</span><br><span>- Do not break shop, game, panic quest, or leaderboard.</span><br><span>- Avoid copying exact Brawl Stars layout/assets. Use original Shift Panic style.</span><br><br><span>Acceptance test:</span><br><span>- Homepage loads without console errors.</span><br><span>- Play Endless works.</span><br><span>- Panic Quest still opens.</span><br><span>- Shop still opens.</span><br><span>- Leaderboard still opens.</span><br><span>- Help still opens.</span><br><span>- No page content is cut off at 1920x1080.</span></code></pre></div></div></div></div></div></div></div></div></div><div class=""><div class="" style="width: 100%; transform: none;"></div></div></div></div></div></pre>
<hr data-start="3679" data-end="3682">
<h1 data-section-id="1uqcjaj" data-start="3684" data-end="3728">PROMPT 2 — Make the Play Button Poki-Level</h1>
<pre class="overflow-visible! px-0!" data-start="3730" data-end="4870"><div class="relative w-full mt-4 mb-1"><div class=""><div class="relative"><div class="h-full min-h-0 min-w-0"><div class="h-full min-h-0 min-w-0" style="width: 100%; transform: none;"><div class="border border-token-border-light border-radius-3xl corner-superellipse/1.1 rounded-3xl"><div class="h-full w-full border-radius-3xl bg-token-bg-elevated-secondary corner-superellipse/1.1 overflow-clip rounded-3xl lxnfua_clipPathFallback"><div class="pointer-events-none absolute end-1.5 top-1 z-2 md:end-2 md:top-1"><button type="button" class="flex gap-1 items-center select-none pointer-events-auto py-2 text-sm font-medium hover:bg-black/5 dark:hover:bg-white/10 size-9 rounded-full px-2" aria-label="Copy" data-state="closed"><svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" width="20" height="20" aria-hidden="true" class="icon-md"><use href="/cdn/assets/sprites-core-0a715c44.svg#ce3544" fill="currentColor"></use></svg></button></div><div class="relative"><div class="pe-11 pt-3" style="transform: none;"><div class="relative z-0 flex max-w-full"><div id="code-block-viewer" dir="ltr" class="q9tKkq_viewer cm-editor z-10 light:cm-light dark:cm-light flex h-full w-full flex-col items-stretch ͼd ͼr"><div class="cm-scroller"><pre class="cm-content q9tKkq_readonly m-0"><code><span>Upgrade the homepage primary CTA buttons to feel like professional arcade game buttons.</span><br><br><span>Current problem:</span><br><span>The Play Endless and Panic Quest buttons are too plain. They do not feel exciting or clickable enough.</span><br><br><span>Make these changes:</span><br><span>1. Make “PLAY ENDLESS” the largest, most obvious button on the homepage.</span><br><span>2. Add a layered gradient, thick border, glossy highlight, soft shadow, and hover scale animation.</span><br><span>3. Add subtle pulsing glow around the Play button every 2–3 seconds.</span><br><span>4. Add a small label above it: “Ready?” or “Start surviving now.”</span><br><span>5. Add keyboard hint only if already supported, but do not clutter the button.</span><br><span>6. Panic Quest should look like a premium blue/purple adventure button with a “NEW” badge.</span><br><span>7. Add hover and active/click feedback to all menu buttons.</span><br><span>8. Make sure buttons are accessible and text remains readable.</span><br><br><span>Do not:</span><br><span>- Break existing click handlers.</span><br><span>- Replace buttons with non-functional divs.</span><br><span>- Add excessive animations that hurt performance.</span><br><br><span>Acceptance test:</span><br><span>- Clicking Play Endless starts endless mode.</span><br><span>- Clicking Panic Quest opens Panic Quest.</span><br><span>- Buttons still work after returning Home from Game Over.</span></code></pre></div></div></div></div></div></div></div></div></div><div class=""><div class="" style="width: 100%; transform: none;"></div></div></div></div></div></pre>
<hr data-start="4872" data-end="4875">
<h1 data-section-id="s1xkee" data-start="4877" data-end="4920">PROMPT 3 — Add Live Gameplay Preview Card</h1>
<pre class="overflow-visible! px-0!" data-start="4922" data-end="6069"><div class="relative w-full mt-4 mb-1"><div class=""><div class="relative"><div class="h-full min-h-0 min-w-0"><div class="h-full min-h-0 min-w-0" style="width: 100%; transform: none;"><div class="border border-token-border-light border-radius-3xl corner-superellipse/1.1 rounded-3xl"><div class="h-full w-full border-radius-3xl bg-token-bg-elevated-secondary corner-superellipse/1.1 overflow-clip rounded-3xl lxnfua_clipPathFallback"><div class="pointer-events-none absolute end-1.5 top-1 z-2 md:end-2 md:top-1"><button type="button" class="flex gap-1 items-center select-none pointer-events-auto py-2 text-sm font-medium hover:bg-black/5 dark:hover:bg-white/10 size-9 rounded-full px-2" aria-label="Copy" data-state="closed"><svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" width="20" height="20" aria-hidden="true" class="icon-md"><use href="/cdn/assets/sprites-core-0a715c44.svg#ce3544" fill="currentColor"></use></svg></button></div><div class="relative"><div class="pe-11 pt-3" style="transform: none;"><div class="relative z-0 flex max-w-full"><div id="code-block-viewer" dir="ltr" class="q9tKkq_viewer cm-editor z-10 light:cm-light dark:cm-light flex h-full w-full flex-col items-stretch ͼd ͼr"><div class="cm-scroller"><pre class="cm-content q9tKkq_readonly m-0"><code><span>Add a “Live Preview” gameplay card to the homepage to make the game feel alive before the user clicks Play.</span><br><br><span>Current problem:</span><br><span>The homepage does not show gameplay clearly. Players should immediately understand the game.</span><br><br><span>Implement:</span><br><span>1. Add a rectangular preview panel inside the homepage hero card.</span><br><span>2. The preview should simulate gameplay visually using lightweight DOM/CSS, not an actual second game loop.</span><br><span>3. Show:</span><br><span>   - A glowing player orb moving slightly left/right.</span><br><span>   - Falling colored blocks.</span><br><span>   - A forbidden color label.</span><br><span>   - Coins floating in.</span><br><span>   - Mini “near miss” or “combo” pop-up occasionally.</span><br><span>4. Preview should loop smoothly and not affect real gameplay state.</span><br><span>5. It should pause or simplify if performance is low.</span><br><span>6. It should not create duplicate timers every time the homepage opens.</span><br><br><span>Important technical requirement:</span><br><span>Create a cleanup mechanism for preview animations/timers when leaving the homepage.</span><br><br><span>Acceptance test:</span><br><span>- Homepage preview animates.</span><br><span>- No console errors.</span><br><span>- Starting real game does not duplicate preview objects.</span><br><span>- Returning from game to home does not create multiple previews stacked on top of each other.</span></code></pre></div></div></div></div></div></div></div></div></div><div class=""><div class="" style="width: 100%; transform: none;"></div></div></div></div></div></pre>
<hr data-start="6071" data-end="6074">
<h1 data-section-id="1s6kqtj" data-start="6076" data-end="6126">PROMPT 4 — Create a Memorable Shift Panic Mascot</h1>
<pre class="overflow-visible! px-0!" data-start="6128" data-end="7077"><div class="relative w-full mt-4 mb-1"><div class=""><div class="relative"><div class="h-full min-h-0 min-w-0"><div class="h-full min-h-0 min-w-0" style="width: 100%; transform: none;"><div class="border border-token-border-light border-radius-3xl corner-superellipse/1.1 rounded-3xl"><div class="h-full w-full border-radius-3xl bg-token-bg-elevated-secondary corner-superellipse/1.1 overflow-clip rounded-3xl lxnfua_clipPathFallback"><div class="pointer-events-none absolute end-1.5 top-1 z-2 md:end-2 md:top-1"><button type="button" class="flex gap-1 items-center select-none pointer-events-auto py-2 text-sm font-medium hover:bg-black/5 dark:hover:bg-white/10 size-9 rounded-full px-2" aria-label="Copy" data-state="closed"><svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" width="20" height="20" aria-hidden="true" class="icon-md"><use href="/cdn/assets/sprites-core-0a715c44.svg#ce3544" fill="currentColor"></use></svg></button></div><div class="relative"><div class="pe-11 pt-3" style="transform: none;"><div class="relative z-0 flex max-w-full"><div id="code-block-viewer" dir="ltr" class="q9tKkq_viewer cm-editor z-10 light:cm-light dark:cm-light flex h-full w-full flex-col items-stretch ͼd ͼr"><div class="cm-scroller"><pre class="cm-content q9tKkq_readonly m-0"><code><span>Create a more memorable original mascot/player identity for Shift Panic on the homepage.</span><br><br><span>Current problem:</span><br><span>The player is just a glowing purple sphere. It is functional but not memorable.</span><br><br><span>Make the homepage show an upgraded “Panic Orb” mascot:</span><br><span>1. Keep it simple and original.</span><br><span>2. Add subtle eyes or expression using CSS/SVG/DOM, not copyrighted assets.</span><br><span>3. Add idle animations:</span><br><span>   - breathing/pulsing glow</span><br><span>   - small hover movement</span><br><span>   - eye blink</span><br><span>   - panic expression when blocks pass nearby in the preview</span><br><span>4. Keep gameplay player unchanged unless the code already uses the same skin renderer safely.</span><br><span>5. Add a label like “Your Runner” or “Panic Orb.”</span><br><span>6. Make it feel like a character players can unlock skins for.</span><br><br><span>Do not:</span><br><span>- Use copyrighted character art.</span><br><span>- Break existing skin system.</span><br><span>- Replace actual gameplay player collision logic.</span><br><br><span>Acceptance test:</span><br><span>- Mascot appears on homepage.</span><br><span>- Animations are smooth.</span><br><span>- No gameplay bugs introduced.</span></code></pre></div></div></div></div></div></div></div></div></div><div class=""><div class="" style="width: 100%; transform: none;"></div></div></div></div></div></pre>
<hr data-start="7079" data-end="7082">
<h1 data-section-id="vuo10a" data-start="7084" data-end="7129">PROMPT 5 — Better Stats + Progression Panel</h1>
<pre class="overflow-visible! px-0!" data-start="7131" data-end="8190"><div class="relative w-full mt-4 mb-1"><div class=""><div class="relative"><div class="h-full min-h-0 min-w-0"><div class="h-full min-h-0 min-w-0" style="width: 100%; transform: none;"><div class="border border-token-border-light border-radius-3xl corner-superellipse/1.1 rounded-3xl"><div class="h-full w-full border-radius-3xl bg-token-bg-elevated-secondary corner-superellipse/1.1 overflow-clip rounded-3xl lxnfua_clipPathFallback"><div class="pointer-events-none absolute end-1.5 top-1 z-2 md:end-2 md:top-1"><button type="button" class="flex gap-1 items-center select-none pointer-events-auto py-2 text-sm font-medium hover:bg-black/5 dark:hover:bg-white/10 size-9 rounded-full px-2" aria-label="Copy" data-state="closed"><svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" width="20" height="20" aria-hidden="true" class="icon-md"><use href="/cdn/assets/sprites-core-0a715c44.svg#ce3544" fill="currentColor"></use></svg></button></div><div class="relative"><div class="pe-11 pt-3" style="transform: none;"><div class="relative z-0 flex max-w-full"><div id="code-block-viewer" dir="ltr" class="q9tKkq_viewer cm-editor z-10 light:cm-light dark:cm-light flex h-full w-full flex-col items-stretch ͼd ͼr"><div class="cm-scroller"><pre class="cm-content q9tKkq_readonly m-0"><code><span>Redesign the homepage stats/progression area to make progression feel rewarding and addictive.</span><br><br><span>Current problem:</span><br><span>Best score, coins, lifetime score, and rank are visible but not exciting. Progression does not feel important.</span><br><br><span>Implement:</span><br><span>1. Create a compact top-right or hero-card stats cluster with:</span><br><span>   - Best score</span><br><span>   - Coins</span><br><span>   - Current rank</span><br><span>   - Lifetime score progress</span><br><span>2. Lifetime score progress should look like a reward track preview:</span><br><span>   - “Next reward: 100 coins”</span><br><span>   - progress bar</span><br><span>   - current lifetime score</span><br><span>3. Add tiny glow/highlight animation when coin count or lifetime score changes.</span><br><span>4. Add a “View Rewards” or “Progress” button that opens the existing progress tab/shop progress area.</span><br><span>5. Make sure data is read from existing storage/state and does not reset.</span><br><br><span>Do not:</span><br><span>- Change the economy.</span><br><span>- Award free coins.</span><br><span>- Reset progress.</span><br><span>- Duplicate progress bars in awkward places.</span><br><br><span>Acceptance test:</span><br><span>- Existing coin count displays correctly.</span><br><span>- Lifetime score displays correctly.</span><br><span>- Clicking View Rewards opens the correct existing progress UI.</span></code></pre></div></div></div></div></div></div></div></div></div><div class=""><div class="" style="width: 100%; transform: none;"></div></div></div></div></div></pre>
<hr data-start="8192" data-end="8195">
<h1 data-section-id="j8h4oa" data-start="8197" data-end="8233">PROMPT 6 — Daily Challenge Upgrade</h1>
<pre class="overflow-visible! px-0!" data-start="8235" data-end="9215"><div class="relative w-full mt-4 mb-1"><div class=""><div class="relative"><div class="h-full min-h-0 min-w-0"><div class="h-full min-h-0 min-w-0" style="width: 100%; transform: none;"><div class="border border-token-border-light border-radius-3xl corner-superellipse/1.1 rounded-3xl"><div class="h-full w-full border-radius-3xl bg-token-bg-elevated-secondary corner-superellipse/1.1 overflow-clip rounded-3xl lxnfua_clipPathFallback"><div class="pointer-events-none absolute end-1.5 top-1 z-2 md:end-2 md:top-1"><button type="button" class="flex gap-1 items-center select-none pointer-events-auto py-2 text-sm font-medium hover:bg-black/5 dark:hover:bg-white/10 size-9 rounded-full px-2" aria-label="Copy" data-state="closed"><svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" width="20" height="20" aria-hidden="true" class="icon-md"><use href="/cdn/assets/sprites-core-0a715c44.svg#ce3544" fill="currentColor"></use></svg></button></div><div class="relative"><div class="pe-11 pt-3" style="transform: none;"><div class="relative z-0 flex max-w-full"><div id="code-block-viewer" dir="ltr" class="q9tKkq_viewer cm-editor z-10 light:cm-light dark:cm-light flex h-full w-full flex-col items-stretch ͼd ͼr"><div class="cm-scroller"><pre class="cm-content q9tKkq_readonly m-0"><code><span>Make the Daily Challenge on the homepage feel like a big arcade feature, not a small boring card.</span><br><br><span>Current problem:</span><br><span>Daily challenge is too small and does not attract clicks.</span><br><br><span>Implement:</span><br><span>1. Create a large “🔥 Daily Challenge” card in the homepage hero area.</span><br><span>2. Show:</span><br><span>   - Challenge title</span><br><span>   - Objective</span><br><span>   - Reward coins</span><br><span>   - Time remaining</span><br><span>   - Progress if applicable</span><br><span>   - “Play Daily” button</span><br><span>3. Add a glowing border and subtle animated shine.</span><br><span>4. If daily challenge is complete, show “Claim Reward” or “Completed” depending on existing logic.</span><br><span>5. The Play Daily button should launch the correct game mode/objective if supported. If not supported yet, route to Endless but clearly track the daily objective using existing challenge logic.</span><br><span>6. Do not create broken claim buttons.</span><br><br><span>Acceptance test:</span><br><span>- Daily challenge displays correctly.</span><br><span>- No duplicate daily challenge cards.</span><br><span>- Claim button only appears when claimable.</span><br><span>- Reward cannot be claimed repeatedly through refresh.</span></code></pre></div></div></div></div></div></div></div></div></div><div class=""><div class="" style="width: 100%; transform: none;"></div></div></div></div></div></pre>
<hr data-start="9217" data-end="9220">
<h1 data-section-id="s8dbe8" data-start="9222" data-end="9255">PROMPT 7 — Desktop Viewport Fix</h1>
<pre class="overflow-visible! px-0!" data-start="9257" data-end="10199"><div class="relative w-full mt-4 mb-1"><div class=""><div class="relative"><div class="h-full min-h-0 min-w-0"><div class="h-full min-h-0 min-w-0" style="width: 100%; transform: none;"><div class="border border-token-border-light border-radius-3xl corner-superellipse/1.1 rounded-3xl"><div class="h-full w-full border-radius-3xl bg-token-bg-elevated-secondary corner-superellipse/1.1 overflow-clip rounded-3xl lxnfua_clipPathFallback"><div class="pointer-events-none absolute end-1.5 top-1 z-2 md:end-2 md:top-1"><button type="button" class="flex gap-1 items-center select-none pointer-events-auto py-2 text-sm font-medium hover:bg-black/5 dark:hover:bg-white/10 size-9 rounded-full px-2" aria-label="Copy" data-state="closed"><svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" width="20" height="20" aria-hidden="true" class="icon-md"><use href="/cdn/assets/sprites-core-0a715c44.svg#ce3544" fill="currentColor"></use></svg></button></div><div class="relative"><div class="pe-11 pt-3" style="transform: none;"><div class="relative z-0 flex max-w-full"><div id="code-block-viewer" dir="ltr" class="q9tKkq_viewer cm-editor z-10 light:cm-light dark:cm-light flex h-full w-full flex-col items-stretch ͼd ͼr"><div class="cm-scroller"><pre class="cm-content q9tKkq_readonly m-0"><code><span>Fix the desktop homepage viewport so it does not feel awkward, cropped, or scroll-heavy.</span><br><br><span>Current problem:</span><br><span>Some important homepage content appears too low or requires scrolling. On desktop, the main menu should feel centered and complete.</span><br><br><span>Implement:</span><br><span>1. At 1920x1080, the main homepage card, title, main buttons, daily challenge, and bottom nav must fit in the first viewport.</span><br><span>2. Remove unnecessary vertical spacing.</span><br><span>3. Make the hero card responsive with max-width and max-height.</span><br><span>4. Use CSS clamp() for title sizes and spacing.</span><br><span>5. Ensure settings button stays top-right but does not overlap content.</span><br><span>6. Prevent horizontal scroll.</span><br><span>7. Keep scroll only if absolutely needed for smaller desktop heights.</span><br><br><span>Acceptance test:</span><br><span>- On 1920x1080, Play Endless, Panic Quest, and secondary nav are visible without scrolling.</span><br><span>- On 1366x768, primary play buttons are still visible.</span><br><span>- No content is cut off behind the Windows taskbar/browser area.</span></code></pre></div></div></div></div></div></div></div></div></div><div class=""><div class="" style="width: 100%; transform: none;"></div></div></div></div></div></pre>
<hr data-start="10201" data-end="10204">
<h1 data-section-id="1auyb3x" data-start="10206" data-end="10245">PROMPT 8 — Homepage Background Polish</h1>
<pre class="overflow-visible! px-0!" data-start="10247" data-end="11214"><div class="relative w-full mt-4 mb-1"><div class=""><div class="relative"><div class="h-full min-h-0 min-w-0"><div class="h-full min-h-0 min-w-0" style="width: 100%; transform: none;"><div class="border border-token-border-light border-radius-3xl corner-superellipse/1.1 rounded-3xl"><div class="h-full w-full border-radius-3xl bg-token-bg-elevated-secondary corner-superellipse/1.1 overflow-clip rounded-3xl lxnfua_clipPathFallback"><div class="pointer-events-none absolute end-1.5 top-1 z-2 md:end-2 md:top-1"><button type="button" class="flex gap-1 items-center select-none pointer-events-auto py-2 text-sm font-medium hover:bg-black/5 dark:hover:bg-white/10 size-9 rounded-full px-2" aria-label="Copy" data-state="closed"><svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" width="20" height="20" aria-hidden="true" class="icon-md"><use href="/cdn/assets/sprites-core-0a715c44.svg#ce3544" fill="currentColor"></use></svg></button></div><div class="relative"><div class="pe-11 pt-3" style="transform: none;"><div class="relative z-0 flex max-w-full"><div id="code-block-viewer" dir="ltr" class="q9tKkq_viewer cm-editor z-10 light:cm-light dark:cm-light flex h-full w-full flex-col items-stretch ͼd ͼr"><div class="cm-scroller"><pre class="cm-content q9tKkq_readonly m-0"><code><span>Polish the homepage animated background so it feels professional instead of random floating blocks.</span><br><br><span>Current problem:</span><br><span>The background is visually related to gameplay, but it feels messy and not intentionally designed.</span><br><br><span>Implement:</span><br><span>1. Keep floating colored blocks but make them feel like a controlled animated scene.</span><br><span>2. Add depth layers:</span><br><span>   - far tiny dim particles</span><br><span>   - mid glowing blocks</span><br><span>   - near blurred danger blocks</span><br><span>3. Reduce opacity behind the main card so text remains readable.</span><br><span>4. Add a subtle radial glow behind the hero card.</span><br><span>5. Add occasional slow color wave across the background.</span><br><span>6. Make animations smooth and lightweight.</span><br><span>7. Respect prefers-reduced-motion if easy.</span><br><br><span>Do not:</span><br><span>- Make background so bright that UI text loses contrast.</span><br><span>- Add large CPU-heavy canvas effects unless already used safely.</span><br><span>- Break gameplay background.</span><br><br><span>Acceptance test:</span><br><span>- Homepage looks more colorful and intentional.</span><br><span>- Text remains readable.</span><br><span>- Performance stays smooth.</span></code></pre></div></div></div></div></div></div></div></div></div><div class=""><div class="" style="width: 100%; transform: none;"></div></div></div></div></div></pre>
