<h1 data-section-id="11yu3io" data-start="12857" data-end="12901">PROMPT 11 — Add First-Time Player Guidance</h1>
<pre class="overflow-visible! px-0!" data-start="12903" data-end="13632"><div class="relative w-full mt-4 mb-1"><div class=""><div class="relative"><div class="h-full min-h-0 min-w-0"><div class="h-full min-h-0 min-w-0" style="width: 100%; transform: none;"><div class="border border-token-border-light border-radius-3xl corner-superellipse/1.1 rounded-3xl"><div class="h-full w-full border-radius-3xl bg-token-bg-elevated-secondary corner-superellipse/1.1 overflow-clip rounded-3xl lxnfua_clipPathFallback"><div class="pointer-events-none absolute end-1.5 top-1 z-2 md:end-2 md:top-1"><button type="button" class="flex gap-1 items-center select-none pointer-events-auto py-2 text-sm font-medium hover:bg-black/5 dark:hover:bg-white/10 size-9 rounded-full px-2" aria-label="Copy" data-state="closed"><svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" width="20" height="20" aria-hidden="true" class="icon-md"><use href="/cdn/assets/sprites-core-0a715c44.svg#ce3544" fill="currentColor"></use></svg></button></div><div class="relative"><div class="pe-11 pt-3" style="transform: none;"><div class="relative z-0 flex max-w-full"><div id="code-block-viewer" dir="ltr" class="q9tKkq_viewer cm-editor z-10 light:cm-light dark:cm-light flex h-full w-full flex-col items-stretch ͼd ͼr"><div class="cm-scroller"><pre class="cm-content q9tKkq_readonly m-0"><code><span>Add a clean first-time player guidance system to the homepage.</span><br><br><span>Goal:</span><br><span>New players should understand Shift Panic in 5 seconds.</span><br><br><span>Implement:</span><br><span>1. Add a small animated “How it works” card or tooltip near the Play button.</span><br><span>2. It should say:</span><br><span>   - “Avoid the forbidden color.”</span><br><span>   - “The forbidden color changes.”</span><br><span>   - “Collect coins and survive longer.”</span><br><span>3. Add a “Try Tutorial” or “Practice Run” button only if tutorial/practice already exists. If not, do not add a broken button.</span><br><span>4. Add a small “?” helper near the title that opens Help.</span><br><span>5. Keep it short and visual, not paragraph-heavy.</span><br><br><span>Acceptance test:</span><br><span>- New users can understand the game from homepage.</span><br><span>- Help opens correctly.</span><br><span>- No fake tutorial button unless implemented.</span></code></pre></div></div></div></div></div></div></div></div></div><div class=""><div class="" style="width: 100%; transform: none;"></div></div></div></div></div></pre>
